UAObject.Description: The ProgramTemplateSetType is a type used for structuring objects of type ProgramTemplateType in an unordered list structure.

The ActiveProgramType specifies the current state of operation of a FunctionalUnit. It provides context and information about the currently active program on the device. This allows users to follow the progress of a program run in a standardized fashion by organising steps into a flat, linear sequence.

UAVariable.Description: EstimatedRuntime is the estimated run-time of the current program run. If the runtime cannot be estimated, the StatusCode BadNoData should be sent.
EstimatedStepNumbers are the estimated total number of steps of the current program run. If the total number cannot be estimated, the StatusCode BadNoData should be sent.
EstimatedStepRuntime is the estimated run-time of the current program-step. If the run-time cannot estimate, the StatusCode BadNoData should sent.

CurrentRuntime is the current run-time of the program -run. The CurrentRunTime is set to 0 at the start of the program and is counted upwards as long as the program run is not in a Paused state. The Paused state is an aggregation of the Suspended state and the Held state.
CurrentStepName is the name of the current step.
CurrentStepNumber is the number/index of the current step (incremented whenever the next step is entered). The CurrentStepNumber starts with 1.

CurrentStepRuntime is the runtime of the current step. The CurrentStepRunTime is set to 0 at the start of the current step and is counted upwards as long as the program run is not in Paused state. The Paused state is an aggregation of the Suspended state and the Held State.
The device specific ID of the current program-run (if any).

UAObject.Description: The ResultSetType is a type used for structuring objects of type ResultType in an unordered list structure.

UAVariable.Description: JobId is the identifier for the execution of a specific workflow, consisting of one or multiple steps. It is provided as an argument Argument of the StartProgram() Method which initiates the program run.

SupervisoryTaskId is the unique identifier of the specific task in the supervisory system to which the result belongs. It is provided as an argument of the StartProgram() Method which initiates the program run.

Properties is a list of key-value pairs with KeyValueType, provided when calling the StartProgram() Method, which can be utilized when performing the program run and provided in the ResultType object for documentation and traceability purposes.

Samples is a list of sample-specific information with SampleInfoType provided when calling the StartProgram() Method, which can be utilized when performing the program run and provided in the ResultType object for documentation and traceability purposes.

UAObject.Description: The ProgramTemplateType provides a program template.

UAVariable.Description: Started is the timestamp of when the program is started.
Stopped is the timestamp of when the program was stopped.
TotalRuntime is the total time of program execution including paused states. Paused states are the held State and the suspended State. This information is retrieved from the ActiveProgramType.

DeviceProgramRunId is the internal program ID assigned by the Device to the ProgramRun to generate this result. It is used to identify a Result object and is returned to the Client when the StartProgram Method is called.
Description is the description of the result set.
Client provides information about the (remote) client which started the program run that generated the result.
User provides information about the (remote) client which started the program run which that generated the result.
